1204C 101st Legislative Session 1204
2026 South Dakota Legislature
House Bill 1204
AMENDME NT 1204C
FOR THE INTRODUCED BILL
Introduced by: Representative Uhre‑Balk
1 An Act to create the South Dakota school building construction fund, provide for the
2 transfer of moneys to the fund, and make an appropriation therefor.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA:
4 Section 1. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 13-24:
5 There is created the South Dakota school building construction loan fund, to be
6 administered by the Department of Education commissioner of school and public lands,
7 for the purpose of making loans to school districts to construct or expand a school building,
8 as provided in section 2 of this Act.
9 Any interest earned on moneys in the fund must remain in the fund. Any repayment
10 of the principal amount of a loan must be deposited into the fund and used for making
11 new loans. Money in the fund designated for loans is continuously appropriated through
12 the general appropriation bill for the purposes provided in section 2 of this Act.
13 The secretary of the department commissioner shall approve vouchers, and the
14 state auditor shall draw warrants to pay expenditures authorized from this fund.
15 Section 2. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 13-24:
16 The Department of Education commissioner of school and public lands may make
17 loans from the South Dakota school building construction fund, created in section 1 of this
18 Act, to a school district for the purpose of constructing or expanding a school building.
19 The amount of the loan may not exceed forty percent of the total cost of the construction
20 or expansion project. The department commissioner may use up to one percent of the
21 principal amount of a loan to offset the department's expenses in administering the loan.
22 Any loan made by the department commissioner must be provided to the district
23 at an interest rate of zero percent. The terms of the loan may not require collateral from
24 the district.
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

1204C 2 1204
1 The terms of the loan must require that the payments be based on a straight and
2 level amortization of twenty years and be made annually over a term of twenty years,
3 with the first payment due one year from the date of the funding of the loan.
4 The department shall make available moneys from the South Dakota school
5 construction fund, created in section 1 of this Act, as follows:
6 (1) Thirty percent for the construction or expansion of a school building in a school
7 district that has four thousand or more students; and
8 (2) Seventy percent for the construction or expansion of a school building in all other
9 school districts.
10 For purposes of this section, a "school building" is a structure that houses the
11 academic instruction, extracurricular activities, and other functions of a kindergarten
12 through twelfth grade educational program.
13 Section 3. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 13-24:
14 A school district is not eligible for a loan under section 2 of this Act if:
15 (1) The school district is eligible for a loan under § 11-15-8; or
16 (2) The municipality in which the district is headquartered is less than ten miles from
17 a municipality in which another school district is headquartered; or
18 (3) The school district has a fall enrollment of fewer than two one hundred fifty
19 students and is not designated as a sparse school district, as defined in § 13-13-
20 78.
21 Section 4. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 13-24:
22 The School Finance Accountability Board within the Department of Education
23 commissioner of school and public lands shall promulgate rules, pursuant to chapter 1-
24 26, specifying:
25 (1) The process by which:
26 (a) A school district applies for a loan;
27 (b) The department commissioner reviews, assesses, and approves a school
28 district's application; and
29 (c) The department commissioner disburses a loan to a school district; and
30 (2) The information a school district must provide when applying for a loan pursuant
31 to section 2 of this Act, including:
32 (a) The amount of money currently in the district's capital outlay fund;
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

1204C 3 1204
1 (b) The amount of money the district has transferred and the number of
2 transfers the district has made from the capital outlay fund, pursuant to
3 § 13-16-6 during the previous ten years;
4 (c) The district's current levy for the capital outlay fund;
5 (d) The district's fall enrollment for the current fiscal year; and
6 (e) The enrollment trends of the district during the previous ten years; and
7 (3) The criteria by which the department commissioner assesses a school district's
8 application for a loan in accordance with section 2 of this Act, including:
9 (a) The minimum amount of money, in proportion to the district's fall
10 enrollment, that which must currently be in a district's capital outlay fund;
11 (b) The maximum amount of money a district may have transferred from the
12 capital outlay fund, pursuant to § 13-16-6 during the previous ten years;
13 (c) The maximum levy a district may currently have set for the district's capital
14 outlay fund; and
15 (d) The minimum increase necessary in the district's capital outlay levy to be
16 sufficient for the district to repay the loan.
17 Section 5. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 13-24:
18 On or before August first of each year, the Department of Education commissioner
19 of school and public lands shall submit a report to the special committee, created in § 4-
20 8A-2, detailing the number, amounts, and recipients of loans provided by from the South
21 Dakota school building construction fund created in section 1 of this Act, and other relevant
22 information pertaining to the fund or program, as requested by the committee.
23 Section 6. The state treasurer shall transfer $1 from the general fund to the South Dakota
24 school building construction fund created in section 1 of this Act. The amount transferred in
25 this section is appropriated to the Department of Education commissioner of school and public
26 lands for the purpose described in section 2 of this Act.
27 Section 7. This Act is effective beginning June 30, 2026.
